The latest twister comes after two people died when a tornado hit New Hanover outside Pietermaritzburg. Several homes have also been destroyed. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A second tornado has ripped through KwaZulu-Natal. The South African Weather Service confirmed it, this time in Bergville, near the Drakensberg. There have been no reports of injuries so far. It's the second one this week. On Tuesday, a tornado killed at least two people in New Hanover near Pietermaritzburg. This as Durban braces for more severe storms. READ: Two people killed in KZN house collapse The city's Mayor Mxolisi Kaunda says emergency teams are more than ready to deal with any situation. Schools have been instructed to send pupils not writing exams back home. Heavy rains have been pounding parts of KwaZulu-Natal, triggering floods and blocking off some roads.